<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_cceef30b-9ab5-4c44-abee-d3e4f79e0b52" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>S40C5</sptc><title id="_f9488122-1071-40d6-9e2c-4417e9c4ff06">Daylight sensor and dynamic lighting control device</title><archive-num>2019: Spec J6: 5</archive-num><subclause id="_08ac91e7-5f28-490b-9dac-380216dd7101" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_543446aa-26e2-46d2-98c9-54d0c3a4f2e6">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A daylight sensor and dynamic control device for artificial lighting must<xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:27:00" xt:id="22a698fb-3e7c-4a35-90d6-2f34fa801928"/>, in response to the measured level of available daylight in the range 50<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="22a698fb-3e7c-4a35-90d6-2f34fa801928"/><xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Ian Findlay" xt:dateTime="2024-09-01T13:55:00" xt:id="fab62c74-ab15-4cbf-9de0-61860406c890"/>–<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="fab62c74-ab15-4cbf-9de0-61860406c890"/><xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:27:00" xt:id="e70f15fb-4121-47ba-9f89-a649ff774746"/>1000 lux<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="e70f15fb-4121-47ba-9f89-a649ff774746"/>—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_bbbed95d-d9b0-45ed-bfa5-53a31019858a"><xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:28:00" xt:id="050c0ed1-fde8-4e5e-bf24-733a15ad1b24"/>for high pressure discharge lights, switch lights on and off with a programmable delay and switching differential; and<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="050c0ed1-fde8-4e5e-bf24-733a15ad1b24"/><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:28:00" xt:id="7f749297-112f-4161-b163-4d183c6462fd"/>for switching on and off—<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="7f749297-112f-4161-b163-4d183c6462fd"/><ol xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:45" xt:type="delete"><li xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:45" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:00" xt:id="1a183e5e-b60b-41a8-9764-576e2a7e7da6"/>be capable of having the switching level set point adjusted between 50 and 1000 lux; and<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="1a183e5e-b60b-41a8-9764-576e2a7e7da6"/></li><li xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:45" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:00" xt:id="3015a4ee-d7eb-4432-be83-d91f939a6db8"/>have—<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="3015a4ee-d7eb-4432-be83-d91f939a6db8"/><ol xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:45" xt:type="delete"><li xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:45" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:00" xt:id="e40b3df2-ae5e-4870-9a43-9b080a506ba2"/>a delay of more than 2 minutes; and<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="e40b3df2-ae5e-4870-9a43-9b080a506ba2"/></li><li xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:44" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:29:00" xt:id="cf2bb29b-dcb9-4c8a-af22-b2781a71302c"/>a differential of more than 100 lux for a sensor controlling high pressure discharge lighting, and 50 lux for a sensor controlling other than high pressure discharge lighting; and<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="cf2bb29b-dcb9-4c8a-af22-b2781a71302c"/></li></ol></li></ol></li><li id="_03fdf325-5d34-4725-a744-ff67ad04bf20"><xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:37:00" xt:id="42815677-6519-4366-896a-6034296fd7cf"/>for all other lights, dim continuously or step lighting output down in not less than 4 steps so that the lowest power setting is less than 50% of full power.<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="42815677-6519-4366-896a-6034296fd7cf"/><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:36:00" xt:id="5d30c471-b2e8-4f9e-a819-b71dc6ca41c4"/>for dimmed or stepped switching, be capable of reducing the power consumed by the controlled lighting in proportion to the incident daylight on the working plane either—<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="5d30c471-b2e8-4f9e-a819-b71dc6ca41c4"/><ol xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:37:03" xt:type="delete"><li xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:37:03" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:37:00" xt:id="897eb707-0394-406b-b082-fc5aaed5a753"/>continuously down to a power consumption that is less than 50% of full power; or<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="897eb707-0394-406b-b082-fc5aaed5a753"/></li><li xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:37:02" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:37:00" xt:id="5a304bea-04fe-402d-8552-248c9800d37c"/>in no less than 4 steps down to a power consumption that is less than 50% of full power.<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="5a304bea-04fe-402d-8552-248c9800d37c"/></li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_8a899e1f-72bb-4aef-a3cd-f15f09c0e616" outputclass="subclause" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:31:17" xt:type="delete"><title id="_3b09c1ea-0ecf-4938-b0b2-2e0629576a42" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:31:17" xt:type="delete">SubClause</title><num xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:31:16" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:31:00" xt:id="64e65a72-9cd3-4731-8ccb-75aaaa8796d9"/>2<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="64e65a72-9cd3-4731-8ccb-75aaaa8796d9"/></num><p xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:31:16" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-11T14:31:00" xt:id="3ae2be34-b0ae-4a15-84e6-257b6042e20c"/>Where a daylight sensor and dynamic control device has a manual override switch, the manual override switch must not be able to switch the lights permanently on or bypass the lighting controls.<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="3ae2be34-b0ae-4a15-84e6-257b6042e20c"/></p></subclause></clause>